Step 1- Open the terminal, and type the following code.

            sudo gedit /etc/default/grub
            
Step 2- Add *pci=nomsi* (without asterisk) to GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash"
        
         Before- GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash"
         After - GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash pci=nomsi"
        
Step 3- Save the file. Next, type the following lines in the terminal.

            sudo update-grub
            
        Now, reboot the system. If the problem persists follow the next steps.
        
Step 4- Open the terminal, and type the following line.

            sudo gedit /etc/default/grub
            
Step 5- Change *pci=nomsi* to *pci=noaer* in GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash pci=nomsi"
        
         Before- GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash pci=nomsi"
         After - GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash pci=noaer"
         
Step 6- Save the file. Next, type the following lines in the terminal.

            sudo update-grub
            
        Now, reboot the system.         
        
